To predict peptides that bind to MHC-I, we used a tool from the Immune Epitope Database (IEDB) to calculate half-maximal inhibitory concentration (IC

 50

) values for peptides binding to specific MHC-I molecules. For the binding analysis, all the frequently used alleles (

 http://tools.iedb.org/mhci/

) with a word length of nine residues and a binding affinity < 200 nm were selected for further analysis [       ]. The MHC-NP tool provided by the IEDB server was used to assess the probability that a given peptide was naturally processed and would bind to a given MHC molecule [       ].

The 3D structure of the HLA-B*15:01 (PDB ID:

 5TXS

) was retrieved from the Protein Data Bank (RCSB-PDB) (

 https://www.rcsb.org/

).
